      <hedline>
        <hl1>REMY COINTREAU TO BUY BOLS</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Andrew Ross Sorkin</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Sorkin, Andrew Ross</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>France's Remy Cointreau SA acquires Bols Royal Distilleries for $461 million; graph (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>France's secondlargest liquor and wine company, Remy Cointreau S.A., agreed to buy Bols Royal Distilleries, a Dutch liqueur maker, for 510 million euros, or $461 million. Remy bought Bols Royal Distilleries from CVC Capital Partners Ltd., a privately held company. Shares of Remy fell 4 percent.</p>
        <p>Andrew Ross Sorkin</p>
      </block>
